.DT
set_move_after
DW_wibble creator help
set_move_after

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
set_move_after -  This method sets the speed at which the npc will randomly wander around.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void set_move_after(int after,
                    int rand)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^after%^RESET%^ - the fixed amount of time
%^BOLD%^rand%^RESET%^ - the random amount of time
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/obj/monster.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method sets the speed at which the npc will randomly
wander around.  The npc will wander at the speed:
.EP
.SP 5 5
speed = after + random(rand)
.EP
.SP 5 5
This is called every time the npc sets up for its next move. 

The move zones control which areas the npcs will wander into, a move zone is set on the room and the npcs will only enter rooms which have a matching move zone. If there is no move zone, then the npc will enter any room.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
remove_move_zone(), query_move_zones(), add_move_zone()

.EP

